The story is good, challenging, great graphics and so far no cliches. I have paid a lot more for some games and they seemed to have clinches to make you pay more, this game doesn't. I am enjoying playing.
I want to give it a 5‚≠ê rating, but there is one puzzle (the maze where I have to move the ball around) that I consistently have to skip because nothing rotates. Other than that, I like it a lot.
A very nice challenging game. Fairly logical. Some back and forth but not to bad. I love the hops. So beautiful. Probably the third time I've played this game. Just as enjoyable ea h time.

Not my favorite HOG. I like the storyline but the execution fell flat. A bit buggy, slow loading/responding. On the HOS it was hard to tell what some objects you were supposed to be looking for were because the thumbnail was so small (played on a 10 inch tablet and thats usually not a problem). Didnt like some of the mini games.
Little variation in puzzles, but otherwise ok

Awesome

First time playing the Dark Parables [paid] series. I tried the Sleeping Beauty edition to get a sense of the developers skill & uninstalled it before completing the trial. I only rate games if I'm significantly impressed otherwise it's a waste of my time. And so far I'm impressed with the graphics and the gameplay. The puzzles are reasonably challenging & the  storyline makes sense. A little disappointed with the HO portion. I'd like to see a variety of HO styles such as word find, anagram, silloette, find the difference, match & vanishing to name a few.  I find that picture search for obscure  shapes to build an object both redundant & boring after a while. I'm only on chapter 2 but I hope to see better HO's as I progress. Im looking forward to rest of the series.
Game kept locking up and then kicking me out. Not worth it.
Not always easy to find things quite dark in places. But I have enjoyed playing it.
Good game took me awhile to get used to it but pretty fun different theme than what I usually play  good job
